For the last year, I have immersed myself in learning about the criminal justice system. I visited prisons, met with formerly incarcerated people, and helped with cases of individual injustice - including two death penalty cases. I have met with and am very supportive of Governor Newsom and his decision to help bring an end to the California Death Penalty. Racial bias and unfairness run deep throughout the justice system but especially when it comes to the death penalty. And we should not be okay with the risk that an innocent person could be executed. I hope we can turn toward better solutions that focus more on healing victims of trauma and prioritizing fairness and justice.

For U.S. residents only.
INDICATION
Bonjesta¬Æ is a prescription medicine to treat nausea & vomiting of pregnancy in women who haven‚Äôt improved with change in diet/other non-medicine treatments. Bonjesta¬Æ hasn‚Äôt been studied in children under 18.
LIMITATIONS OF USE
It isn‚Äôt known if Bonjesta¬Æ is safe & effective in women with severe nausea & vomiting of pregnancy (hyperemesis gravidarum). Women with this condition may need to be hospitalized.
SELECT SAFETY INFORMATION
Don‚Äôt take Bonjesta¬Æ if you‚Äôre allergic to doxylamine succinate, other ethanolamine derivative antihistamines, pyridoxine hydrochloride or any ingredients in Bonjesta¬Æ. See Patient Information leaflet for complete list of ingredients. Don‚Äôt take Bonjesta¬Æ in combination with medicines called MAOIs, as these medicines can intensify & prolong adverse central nervous system (CNS) effects of Bonjesta¬Æ. Ask your healthcare provider/pharmacist if you aren‚Äôt sure if you take an MAOI.
The most common side effect of Bonjesta¬Æ is drowsiness. Don‚Äôt drive, operate heavy machinery or do other activities that need your full attention unless your healthcare provider says you can.
Don‚Äôt drink alcohol, or take other CNS depressants such as cough & cold medicines, certain pain medicines & medicines that help you sleep while taking Bonjesta¬Æ. Severe drowsiness can happen or become worse causing falls/accidents. Bonjesta¬Æ may result in false positive urine drug screening for methadone, opiates and PCP.
